#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_concavepolygonshape2d.rst:19
msgid ""
"Concave polygon 2D shape resource for physics. It is made out of segments"
" and is optimal for complex polygonal concave collisions. However, it is "
"not advised to use for :ref:`RigidBody2D <class_RigidBody2D>` nodes. A "
"CollisionPolygon2D in convex decomposition mode (solids) or several "
"convex objects are advised for that instead. Otherwise, a concave polygon"
" 2D shape is better for static collisions."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_concavepolygonshape2d.rst:21
msgid ""
"The main difference between a :ref:`ConvexPolygonShape2D "
"<class_ConvexPolygonShape2D>` and a ``ConcavePolygonShape2D`` is that a "
"concave polygon assumes it is concave and uses a more complex method of "
"collision detection, and a convex one forces itself to be convex in order"
" to speed up collision detection."
msgstr ""

